line_1: By wilder Welchmen led, and crown'd with leeks!
line_2: MARCH various, fierce, and wild, with wind-crack'd cheeks,

line_1: And Allium calls his onions and his leeks;
line_2: He then of Rhus and Rhododendron speaks,

line_1: In Welch women o'er beds of Leeks;
line_2: Such is the language DISCORD speaks
